class Solution {
    public boolean isIsomorphic(String s, String t) {
        HashMap<Character,Character> mpp = new HashMap<>();

        int n = s.length();
        int m = t.length();

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            char orginal = s.charAt(i);
            char replace = t.charAt(i);

            if(!mpp.containsKey(orginal)){
                if(!mpp.containsValue(replace)){
                    mpp.put(orginal,replace);
                }else{
                    return false;
                }
            }else{
                char mapped = mpp.get(orginal);
                if(mapped != replace){
                    return false;
                }
            }

        }
        return true;
    }
}

Two strings are isomorphic if a one-to-one mapping is possible for every character of the first string ‘str1’ to every character of the second string ‘str2’ while preserving the order of the characters.



Sample Input 1 :
aab 
xxy
Sample Output 1 :
true
Explanation of sample input 1:
The character ‘a’ maps to ‘x’ and ‘b’ maps to ‘y’. Hence, the answer is true in this case.

Sample Input 2 :
aab
xyz
Sample Output 2 :
false
